pr_title: [#9536] Instructor Course Edit Page E2E Test

timeline.message: Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jtankw3/teammates into instructor-course-edit-e2e

timeline.bodyText:
Why is this status message hardcoded? I think it should be programatically derived.
If not, the test is brittle and any small change in the message (an extra space etc.) will break the E2E tests.
The same applies to the other status messages.
timeline.author: rrtheonlyone

replies.bodyText:
This is actually a grey area. On one hand, what you said is of course true. However, on the other hand, this is a black-box test, meaning that the test code should not actually know that there exists some constant in the code that holds that string.
Either way is acceptable.
replies.author: wkurniawan07

replies.bodyText: I did not use the Const values as they are Deprecated. I have added tried to use variables instead for names, emails etc in the status message instead to try to make is slightly less brittle.
replies.author: jtankw3

timeline.bodyText: In this test case, we add a new instructor and verify that the frontend has the instructor's details. However, the backend is not verified right? We should also check that the database has the new instructor in this course.
timeline.author: rrtheonlyone

replies.bodyText: Added some methods with Backdoor to do some verification for backend
replies.author: jtankw3

timeline.bodyText: Same for this test case. The backend is not verified. Actually this point holds throughout for the other test cases!
timeline.author: rrtheonlyone
